            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> Even when reproducer running under python 3.14 is not correct. As mentioned above it should raise `TypeError`\n\nMaybe, but that would be a change compared to previous Cython versions. The main issue I am reporting here is a regression in Cython 3.3.0a1 which results in either a segfault or faulty code generation.\n\nSome people have added Python-style type annotations in python-flint like `list[int]` rather than Cython ones like `cdef list`. I don't understand exactly how Cython does or does not use these type annotations but this isn't the first time I've opened a Cython issue related to them.\n\nThe type `list[int]` cannot be expressed with `cdef` type declarations and is tricky because it is not runtime checkable: do you iterate over the whole list? What about mutability? I imagine that what happens here is the segfault comes from something assuming that the elements of the list are of type `int` without checking that at runtime (e.g. casting a `PyObject*` to `PyLong*` with no `p->ob_type` check). That would explain why the segfault goes away if I change `list[int]` to `list` in the annotation.",
