        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Cython 3.3.0a1 is intending to start using the element types for `list[int]` type annotations (where previous Cython versions never looked further than `list`).\n\nThe general rule is that the type-checks are done on element access and that hasn't happened correctly in your example.\n\nI think (but haven't tested) that if you'd written the iteration as:\n\n```\nfor n in N:\n   if n < 0:\n      return True\n   return False\n```\n\nthen it probably would have given you a `TypeError` on reaching the first non-`int` element (and that this is the intended behaviour for Cython 3.3.0a1)",
